## Brand voice & UI

- **Font:** Outfit (Google Font), loaded via `globals.css`.
- **Palette:** defined as CSS variables in `globals.css` — see CSS variable section below.
- **Copy:** Lives in WordPress CMS. Do not hardcode product claims; match existing conversion-oriented tone (clear, professional, benefit-led).
- **Motion:** GSAP + `@gsap/react`. Scroll-triggered stagger uses the `REVEAL_ITEM` class (see Animation section).

---

## CSS variable conventions

Two-layer system in `globals.css`:

**Layer 1 — raw palette on `:root`:**
```
--palette-white: #ffffff
--palette-brand: #3990f0
--palette-brand-strong: #0569d7
--palette-navy: #152951
--palette-navy-deep: #002752
--palette-muted: #435780
--palette-surface: #ebf3fe
--palette-card: #ebf3fe
--palette-pill: #ecf4fe
--palette-accent: #1d5898
--palette-brand-soft: #3a8ae4
--palette-rose: #d27e91
--palette-rose-soft: #ca7c90
--palette-showcase-blush: #fadbe9
--palette-showcase-mint: #cceded
--palette-showcase-gold-wash: rgba(200,148,2,0.28)
--palette-star: #f97316
```

**Layer 2 — Tailwind tokens (`@theme inline`):**
`--color-brand`, `--color-navy`, `--color-navy-deep`, `--color-muted`, `--color-surface`, `--color-card`, `--color-pill`, `--color-accent`, `--color-rose`, `--font-sans`

**Rules:**
- Use `--palette-*` or `--color-*` variables only. **No hardcoded hex values** in components.
- Tailwind utility classes (`text-brand`, `bg-navy-deep`, `bg-surface`, etc.) are preferred over raw CSS vars for standard values.
- No `tailwind.config.*` file — Tailwind v4 is configured entirely via `@theme inline` in `globals.css`.

